$ Oracle PL/SQL: PRAGMA UDF

A function can be declared with the `PRAGMA UDF` which tells the compiler that this function is a *user defined function*.

Declaring a function as used defined function might improve the function's response time when used in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement[SQL statements].

